==English==
===Etymology===
From ''[[seat]]'' + ''[[belt]]''.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈsi:tbɛlt/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A strap fastened across the body of someone travelling in a [[car]] or other vehicle, designed to hold them in place in the event of a crash.

